WHY THIS LICENSE (note, not legally operative)
A permissive open-source license (e.g. MIT) would place the code in the public domain of
use and could weaken a future utility-solution/patent claim. The Apache-2.0 license includes
an explicit patent grant, which is likewise undesirable while patentability is being assessed.
"All rights reserved" keeps options open. The copyright holders MAY later relicense the Work
(for example under MIT or Apache-2.0 for the software, while protecting the novel mechanism
separately) once the IP strategy is decided — see docs/10-improvements.md and docs/09-roadmap.md.

